<chapter>
<num>CHAPTER 729—</num>
<heading>MISCELLANEOUS PROHIBITIONS AND PENALTIES</heading>
<section>
<num>§ 7239.</num>
<heading> Enlisted members: officers not to use as servants</heading>
<content>
<p class="indent0">No officer of the Army may use an enlisted member of the Army as a servant.</p>
</content>
<sourceCredit>(<ref>Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref>70A Stat. 208</ref>, § 3639; renumbered § 7239, <ref>Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(b)(8)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref>132 Stat. 1838</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
